2 years ago, I set out to develop a brand that would go beyond selling haircare products; I wanted to start a movement. The goal was simple: create a wellness ritual that would support you with embracing your confidence, nurturing your hair from the inside out and, above all, taking the time to cherish yourself.

Burgeon is a culmination of years of research and experience, a commitment to our beautiful planet, and a dedication to feeling your absolute best.

And we launch… tomorrow! 

Follow us @burgeon.hair to join the movement. And stay tuned. 

xx
Laini

Posted @withregram • @amazingmagazine Brit Marling is taking her rightful place in the director’s chair with new FX series A Murder at the End of the World, which unflinchingly tackles the highly topical issues of artificial intelligence, misogyny and violence against women, in one hot-blooded whodunnit starring @emmalouisecorrin.

“The goal was to write a hot-blooded mystery,” says Marling. “I love mystery as a genre, but they tend to be cold and cerebral. I love solving a good puzzle, but we wanted to make something that was working out your mind and working out your heart, so that by the end of it you’re really having all the big feels.”

For Brit’s full interview and shoot, order your copy of AMAZING issue 4 at theamazingmagazine.com now. A Murder at the End of the World streams on hulu in the US and on Disney+ in the UK.

get. the. look. 
prepping Emily’s hair started well before the big day. She’s been using @burgeon.hair for the last two months to increase radiance and volume, and her results have been fantastic! For tonight, I first applied  the @burgeon.hair scalp treatment on wet hair, I then applied @yaman.usa hair oil on to seal the ends. Then using the @yaman.usa hairdryer I power dried Emily’s hair. 

Next, I put Emily’s hair in a high ponytail and braided it.  I then secured the braid with bobby pins tied the ends with a gold thread.
Then I took the top section of Emily’s hair made another ponytail then flat ironed the ends using the @yaman.usa flat iron. Next I made a messy bun to sit on top of the braid.
I then decorated with the @tiffanyandco  broach’s.
#emilyblunt #asm_mgmt #LainiReeves
